# 1. Add CSS comments in your CSS block.
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Tata Group of Industries</title>
    <style>
        /* Set background color for the page */
        body {
            background-color: #f4f4f4; /* Light gray */
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif; /* Default font */
            margin: 20px; /* Add space around the page */
            padding: 20px; /* Add padding inside */
        }

        /* Styling for the heading */
        h1 {
            color: #2c3e50; /* Dark blue */
            text-align: center; /* Center align */
            font-size: 32px; /* Set font size */
            font-weight: bold; /* Make text bold */
        }

        /* Styling for the paragraph */
        p {
            font-size: 18px; /* Set font size */
            color: #555; /* Medium gray text */
            text-align: justify; /* Justify text */
            line-height: 1.6; /* Improve readability */
            margin: 20px auto; /* Center the text block */
            width: 80%; /* Set width of the paragraph */
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

    <h1>Tata Group of Industries</h1>
    <p>
        Tata Group is one of India's largest and most respected conglomerates, known for its ethical leadership, 
        innovation, and global presence. Founded by Jamsetji Tata in 1868, it has expanded into diverse industries, 
        including steel, automobiles, IT, and telecommunications. Under the leadership of Ratan Tata, the group 
        acquired international brands like Jaguar Land Rover and Corus Steel, further strengthening its global footprint.
    </p>

</body>
</html>

# 2. Create a page with different background-colour of a page and set an image as the background-image of a page (image should not scroll with the rest of the page and specify the size of a background image)
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Background Image Example</title>
    <style>
      
        body {
            background-color: #f4f4f4; 
            background-image: url('https://hbr.org/resources/images/article_assets/2024/08/R2405L_BLINDSALIDA.png'); 
            background-size: 100%,100%;  
            background-position: center; 
            background-attachment: fixed; 
        }

       
        .content {
            width: 80%;
            margin: 50px auto;
            padding: 20px;
            background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.8); 
            border-radius: 10px;
            box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.2);
            text-align: center;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

    <div class="content">
        <h1>Welcome to My Page</h1>
        <p>This page has your requirements.And for the image you should look at the page at 100%. It helps you to view the page correctly.</p>
    </div>

</body>
</html>

# 3. Create a different page with the width, style and color of the 4 border-style(set different borders on each side with different patterns).
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Border Styles Example</title>
    <style>
        /* Styling the container with different borders */
        .border-box {
            width: 400px;
            padding: 20px;
            margin: 50px auto;
            text-align: center;
            font-size: 18px;
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            
            /* Applying different border styles */
            border-top: 5px solid red;      /* Solid border on top */
            border-right: 8px dashed blue;  /* Dashed border on right */
            border-bottom: 10px double green; /* Double border at bottom */
            border-left: 6px dotted orange; /* Dotted border on left */
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

    <div class="border-box">
        <h2>Different Borders on Each Side</h2>
        <p>This box has different border styles, colors, and widths on each side.</p>
    </div>

</body>
</html>

# 4. Develop a page and set the height:(in pixels and %) and width:(in pixels and %) on elements.
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Height and Width Example</title>
    <style>
        
        .full-screen {
            width: 100%;
            height: 100vh; 
            background-color: #f4f4f4;
            display: flex;
            justify-content: center;
            align-items: center;
        }

        
        .content-box {
            width: 50%; 
            height: 300px; 
            background-color: white;
            text-align: center;
            padding: 20px;
            border: 2px solid #333;
            box-shadow: 0 4px 8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.2);
        }

   
        .inner-box {
            width: 80%; 
            height: 50%; 
            background-color: lightblue;
            margin: auto;
            line-height: 150px; 
            font-weight: bold;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

    <div class="full-screen">
        <div class="content-box">
            <h2>Height & Width</h2>
            <p>Using pixels and percentages.</p>
            <div class="inner-box">we can see the output of your question clearly.</div>
        </div>
    </div>

</body>
</html>

# 5. Develop a page with different font-styles, font-size, font-family, colors and text-align.
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Text Styling Example</title>
    <style>
        /* General body styling */
        body {
            background-color: #f4f4f4;
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            padding: 20px;
        }

        /* Heading styles */
        h1 {
            font-family: 'Georgia', serif;
            font-size: 40px;
            color: #e74c3c;
            text-align: center;
            font-style: italic;
        }

        h2 {
            font-family: 'Courier New', monospace;
            font-size: 30px;
            color: #3498db;
            text-align: left;
            font-weight: bold;
        }

        /* Paragraph styles */
        p {
            font-family: 'Verdana', sans-serif;
            font-size: 18px;
            color: #333;
            text-align: justify;
            line-height: 1.6;
        }

        /* Special text with different styles */
        .highlight {
            font-size: 22px;
            color: #2ecc71;
            font-style: oblique;
            font-weight: bold;
            text-align: right;
        }

        /* Center-aligned text */
        .center-text {
            font-size: 24px;
            color: #8e44ad;
            text-align: center;
            font-weight: bold;
        }

        /* Styled link */
        a {
            font-size: 18px;
            color: #e67e22;
            text-decoration: none;
            font-weight: bold;
        }

        a:hover {
            text-decoration: underline;
        }

        /* Footer styling */
        .footer {
            font-size: 16px;
            color: #777;
            text-align: center;
            margin-top: 40px;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

    <h1>Welcome to My Stylish Page</h1>
    <h2>Typography and Text Styling Example</h2>

    <p>
        This is a paragraph with a <strong>Verdana</strong> font, 18px size, and justified text alignment. 
        The text has proper <span class="highlight">line spacing</span> to improve readability.
    </p>

    <p class="highlight">This is an oblique-styled text aligned to the right.</p>

    <p class="center-text">This text is bold, 24px, and centered.</p>

    <p>Want to learn more? <a href="#">Click here</a> for more details.</p>

    <div class="footer">
        Â© 2025 My Stylish Page. All Rights Reserved.
    </div>

</body>
</html>
